OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FClifford previously admitted three
OL,8,Fcounts of murder, one of false
OL,9,Fimprisonment against Louise Hunt, and
OL,10,Ftwo counts of possession of offensive
OL,11,Fweapons - the crossbow and the knife.
OL,13,FAfter hearing part of the
OL,14,Fprosecution's case, trial judge Mr
OL,15,FJustice Bennathan urged jurors to
OL,16,Fremain "calm and collected" despite
OL,17,Fthe shocking events, reminding them to
OL,18,Ffocus on the rape charge.
OL,20,FClifford currently denies a single
OL,21,Fcharge of rape.
